name: Niketan Patel
tweet: there were also incredibly unlikely events in my favor: * flopping quads * runner runner two pair * flopping a straight twice with 65o  hella wide variance. crazy lololol.  this frequency of unlikely events is something i think you‚Äôll almost never see in the markets.

name: Niketan Patel
tweet: in trading, it‚Äôs more in your control to limit the frequency of unlikely events by deployment.  i‚Äôve now seen a new level of unlucky. the bright side is that it mathematically can‚Äôt get much worse than this. i haven‚Äôt had my quads beaten by a straight flush... yet. üòÇ

name: Niketan Patel
tweet: in other words, i got smashed in poker tn in many ways:  * op flopped a boat when i had 2 pair * op flopped a straight flush when i had nut flush draw * got rekt on the river like 3 times  in a single night, it‚Äôs impressive how many of these incredibly unlikely events can happen.

name: Niketan Patel
tweet: one thing different between poker and trading is  in poker you‚Äôre forced to be exposed to very wide variance, like hella black swans.  in trading you can generally control the width of variance based on where you choose to deploy capital.
